COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 11:38AM PT today, over 1.7 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 28.1 thousand have died.

In the last day, 1.6 thousand new infections were reported and 26 deaths. Currently 2,540 are in the hospital and 763 are in the ICU. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 56.7 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 11.6% have their 1st shot and 18.3% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 7.7 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~94 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Nov-17 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
